      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/BusinessCenters
          description: |
            A class for specifying the business day calendar location used in determining whether a day is a business day or not, either by specifying this business center by reference to an enumerated list that is maintained by the FpML standard, or by reference to such specification when it exists elsewhere as part of the instance document. This class corresponds to the FpML BusinessCentersOrReference.model.
          businessCenter:
            description: |
              A code identifying one or several business day calendar location(s). The set of business day calendar locations are specified by the business day calendar location enumeration which is maintained by the FpML standard.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: EtUp3RuaDWzJnGNfgdjWD82gBrcgUyd6KM7cMfBajMzy
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          businessCentersReference:
            description: A reference to a financial business center location specified elsewhere in the instance document.
            type:
              blueId: 7ACnecbuWHtBLYhrw8BaioS3DSUQFiDskjpaDNspEmof
          commodityBusinessCalendar:
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: 8TYiPxS12nea35y6YR9jrThpiNyYMJgNPgJCd6hF3T1i
            schema:
              minItems: 0
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: H53mV1d8rMzhefLZH8WzGchozyQA28cbwNpBHGmVA9ti
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/BusinessCenterTime
          description: A class for defining a time with respect to a business day calendar location. For example, 11:00:00 GBLO.
          businessCenter:
            description: |
              A code identifying a business day calendar location. A business day calendar location is drawn from the list identified by the business day calendar location enumeration.
            type:
              blueId: EtUp3RuaDWzJnGNfgdjWD82gBrcgUyd6KM7cMfBajMzy
            schema:
              required: true
          hourMinuteTime:
            description: |
              A time specified in hh:mm:ss format where the second component must be '00', e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 4Mi73c2rJbGTBeaTVi4xUgW33QBxsUyxSSV6ELoqnP4j
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/BusinessDateRange
          description: |
            A class defining a range of contiguous business days by defining an unadjusted first date, an unadjusted last date and a business day convention and business centers for adjusting the first and last dates if they would otherwise fall on a non business day in the specified business centers. The days between the first and last date must also be good business days in the specified centers to be counted in the range.
          businessCenters:
            description: |
              The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
            type:
              blueId: H53mV1d8rMzhefLZH8WzGchozyQA28cbwNpBHGmVA9ti
          businessDayConvention:
            description: |
              The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day, as specified by an ISDA convention (e.g. Following, Precedent).
            type:
              blueId: UEYhmdmBmLhrdtL1ThGtACP6Ljtvao5EVBeQdbiB2XJ
            schema:
              required: true
          endDate:
            description: The last date of a date range.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          startDate:
            description: The first date of a date range.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: HNjhMn7WT4JjM4LH3CAB6FzPpLMvur9mQW6knri1HnTg
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/BusinessDayAdjustments
          description: |
            A class defining the business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day in the specified business center.
          businessCenters:
            description: |
              The business center(s), specified either explicitly or by reference to those specified somewhere else in the instance document.
            type:
              blueId: H53mV1d8rMzhefLZH8WzGchozyQA28cbwNpBHGmVA9ti
          businessDayConvention:
            description: The convention for adjusting a date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business day.
            type:
              blueId: UEYhmdmBmLhrdtL1ThGtACP6Ljtvao5EVBeQdbiB2XJ
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8ZhZC2EwhTqHnDvvcr2ZW4iwCBJM57NcLAqPCd8shypq
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/BusinessDayConventionEnum
          description: |
            The enumerated values to specify the convention for adjusting any relevant date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a valid business day.
          type:
            blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          schema:
            enum:
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: FOLLOWING
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: FRN
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: MODFOLLOWING
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: MODPRECEDING
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: NEAREST
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: NONE
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: NotApplicable
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: PRECEDING
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: UEYhmdmBmLhrdtL1ThGtACP6Ljtvao5EVBeQdbiB2XJ
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/CalculationFrequency
          description: |
            Represents the parameters for describing how often something (such as collateral interest) is to be calculated.
          businessCenter:
            description: Specifies the business center for adjustment of calculation period.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: Ftpos6LCMk31PB3e4E1siiMshU1M88BMeTNK4yRypXyL
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          dateLocation:
            description: Specifies where is the time measured.
            type:
              blueId: 4Mi73c2rJbGTBeaTVi4xUgW33QBxsUyxSSV6ELoqnP4j
            schema:
              required: true
          dayOfMonth:
            description: Specifies the day of the month if used.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          dayOfWeek:
            description: Specifies the day of the week if used.
            type:
              blueId: AYNVNBQsDmS46NA7kfw7jh6eh8DBspyMyDd1bzyBmDG5
          monthOfYear:
            description: Specifies the month of the year if used.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          offsetDays:
            description: Specifies how many days from the trigger event should the payment occur.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
            schema:
              required: true
          period:
            description: Specifies the time period at which calculation is performed, e.g. 1 month.
            type:
              blueId: G5BwzTWEaA14NoPKn8iSwCnmwnWuQegPHZwrpgagS6kY
            schema:
              required: true
          weekOfMonth:
            description: Specifies the week of the month if used.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: DgNkH6r165bjLKnYWiVE6o2FPj5mEztGpd21mfsiyDXA
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/base/datetime/CalculationPeriodFrequency
          description: |
            A class to specify the frequency at which calculation period end dates occur within the regular part of the calculation period schedule and their roll date convention.
          balanceOfFirstPeriod:
            description: |
              Indicates, when true, that that the first Calculation Period should run from the Effective Date to the end of the calendar period in which the Effective Date falls, e.g. Jan 15 - Jan 31 if the calculation periods are one month long and Effective Date is Jan 15. If false, the first Calculation Period should run from the Effective Date for one whole period, e.g. Jan 15 to Feb 14 if the calculation periods are one month long and Effective Date is Jan 15. Mostly used in Commmodity Swaps.
            type:
              blueId: AwvXD961fmnmqcSQhjMA7r15HpVh39cefb6ZTyUz2Fm2
          period:
            description: A time period, e.g. a day, week, month, year or term of the stream.
            type:
              blueId: BLwQ9sW7unThpYZC3TVs8YtMmiAoZ4NVGjVRppu4gm7x
          periodMultiplier:
            description: |
              A time period multiplier, e.g. 1, 2, or 3. If the period value is T (Term) then period multiplier must contain the value 1.
            type:
              blueId: E2LM6qgzWG9ttagq2xTmiZkgYEAgkYedFCmU9v7NnVEq
          rollConvention:
            description: |
              The roll convention specifies the period term as part of a periodic schedule, i.e. the calculation period end date within the regular part of the calculation period. The value could be a rule, e.g. IMM Settlement Dates, which is the 3rd Wednesday of the month, or it could be a specific day of the month, such as the first day of the applicable month. It is used in conjunction with a frequency and the regular period start date of a calculation period.
            type:
              blueId: 5vi7aU3GvfLQ4xDo1Ud6tENVfH6eddFwtnAbqXHuxMfi
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: CkosQzywFhAU6NAYFKUn1Q9gvuL9kvbk3rfWxAdrAsce
            attributesAdded: []
