          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: HZmoSFgPTJDpgvQbhrw415z735PsqkkNK7AhockdXE35
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/event/workflow/EventInstruction
          description: Specifies instructions to create a BusinessEvent.
          corporateActionIntent:
            type:
              blueId: GFvEqH3FNnzTFFJAqMgygUiVX9vA45GDjiV95ZqP4qAR
          effectiveDate:
            description: The date on which the event contractually takes effect, when different from the event date.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          eventDate:
            description: |
              Specifies the date on which the event is taking place. This date is equal to the trade date in the case of a simple execution.  However it can be different from the trade date, for example in the case of a partial termination.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          instruction:
            description: Specifies the instructions to create the Business Event.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: GEHuJ1Fk1jSrDMfbynCACW1dsPVuMhSkjFbkitJU37Qp
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          intent:
            description: |
              The intent attribute is meant to be specified when the event qualification cannot be programmatically inferred from the event features. As a result it is only associated with those primitives that can give way to such ambiguity, the quantityChange being one of those. An example of such is a reduction in the trade notional, which could be interpreted as either a trade correction (unless a maximum period of time post-event is specified as part of the qualification), a partial termination or a portfolio rebalancing in the case of an equity swap. On the other hand, an event such as the exercise is not expected to have an associated intent as there should not be ambiguity.
            type:
              blueId: 3eSk21DN6a3UUApaPYyPtqi3HPeLX7zYga6PMuXULqNa
          packageInformation:
            description: |
              Specifies the package information in case the business event represents several trades executed as a package (hence this attribute is optional). The package information is only instantiated once at the business event level to preserve referential integrity, whereas individual trades make reference to it to identify that they are part of a package.
            type:
              blueId: Dq7xVZaLz1ofmKsUodtSSbe6YGxaRdCtP5HM1pKU8RHF
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: A1jYzNcEp75NaNXNyvEb5S2noXSa3PnFck4qj5Cdvuvs
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/event/workflow/EventTimestamp
          description: |
            A class to represent the various set of timestamps that can be associated with lifecycle events, as a collection of [dateTime, qualifier].
          dateTime:
            description: |
              The CDM specifies that the zoned date time is to be expressed in accordance with ISO 8601, either as UTC as an offset to UTC.
            type:
              blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
            schema:
              required: true
          qualification:
            description: |
              The timestamp qualifier is specified through an enumeration because the experience of integrating the DTCC and CME data representations suggests that a wide set of timestamps are currently utilized among service providers, while there is not at present an objective set of criteria that could help suggest a defined set of timestamps as part of the CDM. At some future point, one possible baseline could be developed from the review of the set of timestamps specified across regulatory regimes and regulations (incl. regulations such as high frequency trading). Also, the integration with a further set of implementations and the specification of business workflows such as clearing as part of the CDM development should help confirm the implementation approach in this respect.
            type:
              blueId: 98uPvPckZ92oJWmjF6PjWKjL2AQpfcZkKBFUSXjnaWdu
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: DSJDCMX9fWnAZqseXHzuc3NWEvtct9Ay1D8XqV7Cz8sb
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/event/workflow/EventTimestampQualificationEnum
          description: |
            The enumeration values to qualify the timestamps that can be associated with a lifecycle event. The reason for such approach is that the experience of integrating the DTCC and CME data representations suggests that a wide set of timestamps are currently utilized among service providers, while there is not at present an objective set of criteria that could help suggest a defined set of timestamps as part of the CDM. Implementers are expected to evaluate the current enumeration values to determine whether those meet their requirements. If not, they are expected to engage with the CDM team to evaluate the addition of further value(s) to this enumeration, which will then participate to the development of a compendium for further evaluation at a later point in order to determine whether this modeling is appropriate.
          type:
            blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          schema:
            enum:
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: clearingConfirmationDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: clearingDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: clearingReceiptDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: clearingSubmissionDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: confirmationDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: eventCreationDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: eventExpirationDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: eventProcessingDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: eventSentDateTime
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
