      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/common/settlement/AssetFlowBase
          description: |
            Defines the basic parameters of an asset transfer, e.g. a cashflow: what (the asset), how much (the quantity) and when (the settlement date).
          asset:
            description: Represents the object that is subject to the transfer, it could be an asset or a reference.
            type:
              blueId: 5UGws2rghMXJPsBC2YMTqJQgztQ8nTZm1XTaGkvxheXo
            schema:
              required: true
          quantity:
            description: |
              Represents the amount of the asset to be transferred. The cashflow amount is always a positive number, as the cashflow direction is implied by the payer/receiver attribute.
            type:
              blueId: BoLMyAuLAegX9RWR7trQbdmp7pB2tAfkPhDoTzbu8acd
            schema:
              required: true
          settlementDate:
            description: Represents the date on which the transfer to due.
            type:
              blueId: 8VijgDyT9t9CiNbNQYVbdE1whbL9Q9DTRMZpCocVhSxF
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: DDpzEiQvyGjc3WViRctaB8EJPZHGTbbpLManidhjUsxW
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/common/settlement/Cashflow
          description: |
            Class to specify a cashflow, i.e. the outcome of either of computation (e.g. interest accrual) or an assessment of some sort (e.g. a fee). The cashflow can then be turned into a cash transfer, artefact to be used as the input to a payment system or the outcome of it. The associated globalKey denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the Cashflow instantiations for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
          asset:
            description: Represents the object that is subject to the transfer, it could be an asset or a reference.
            type:
              blueId: 5UGws2rghMXJPsBC2YMTqJQgztQ8nTZm1XTaGkvxheXo
          cashflowType:
            description: |
              The qualification of the type of cashflow, e.g. brokerage fee, premium, upfront fee etc. Particularly relevant when it cannot be inferred directly through lineage.
            type:
              blueId: GArm2fDK1vopaSHjgRguRRS1k6GiHBGUifjuhdbJEfg
            schema:
              required: true
          payerReceiver:
            description: Specifies who pays / receives the cashflow, though a normalised Party1 / Party2 enumerator.
            type:
              blueId: 3xPof2WJyFXisFtvaxpSGddTxHyGioazbsMJjuUucbzT
            schema:
              required: true
          paymentDiscounting:
            description: |
              FpML specifies the FpML PaymentDiscounting.model group for representing the discounting elements that can be associated with a payment.
            type:
              blueId: 9dkTzBV6xqQ9LmULZCPBAZi5Afj3tZytwUtqXc1iccwt
          quantity:
            description: |
              Represents the amount of the asset to be transferred. The cashflow amount is always a positive number, as the cashflow direction is implied by the payer/receiver attribute.
            type:
              blueId: BoLMyAuLAegX9RWR7trQbdmp7pB2tAfkPhDoTzbu8acd
          settlementDate:
            description: Represents the date on which the transfer to due.
            type:
              blueId: 8VijgDyT9t9CiNbNQYVbdE1whbL9Q9DTRMZpCocVhSxF
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 3vRMCGh2M3Ggi4kWVbmZ85TLuo1A54NFwDCbhvAZt9XA
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/common/settlement/CashflowType
          description: |
            Characterises the type of cashflow, which can result from either a scheduled or a non-scheduled lifecycle event.
          cashflowType:
            description: Type of cashflow corresponding to a scheduled event.
            type:
              blueId: 9k43VLjjoSJbXKM7aCSjBTinwWFf8sRDogVJbsM2JjjR
          cashPrice:
            description: Type of cashflow corresponding to a non-scheduled event, where a price must be agreed between the parties.
            type:
