            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/MultipleExercise
          description: |
            A class defining multiple exercises. As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.4. Multiple Exercise, the buyer of the option has the right to exercise all or less than all the unexercised notional amount of the underlying swap on one or more days in the exercise period, but on any such day may not exercise less than the minimum notional amount or more than the maximum notional amount, and if an integral multiple amount is specified, the notional exercised must be equal to or, be an integral multiple of, the integral multiple amount. In FpML, MultipleExercise is built upon the PartialExercise.model.
          integralMultipleAmount:
            description: |
              A notional amount which restricts the amount of notional that can be exercised when partial exercise or multiple exercise is applicable. The integral multiple amount defines a lower limit of notional that can be exercised and also defines a unit multiple of notional that can be exercised, i.e. only integer multiples of this amount can be exercised.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          maximumNotionalAmount:
            description: The maximum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          maximumNumberOfOptions:
            description: |
              The maximum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date. If the number is not specified, it means that the maximum number of options corresponds to the remaining unexercised options.
            type:
              blueId: E2LM6qgzWG9ttagq2xTmiZkgYEAgkYedFCmU9v7NnVEq
          minimumNotionalAmount:
            description: The minimum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date. See multipleExercise.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          minimumNumberOfOptions:
            description: The minimum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date.
            type:
              blueId: E2LM6qgzWG9ttagq2xTmiZkgYEAgkYedFCmU9v7NnVEq
          notionaReference:
            description: |
              A pointer style reference to the associated notional schedule defined elsewhere in the document. This element has been made optional as part of its integration in the OptionBaseExtended, because not required for the options on securities.
            type:
              blueId: EP1r4ouVVbfJhEazX6iBArCJYk3u6aP7hwxJSGLBFbet
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8eLP8HxgpSvj1vyxDJXMhDpMcQU696aKo5Uvz1mt9Q1S
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/NonTransferableProduct
          description: |
            A data type to specify the financial product's economic terms, alongside the product identification and product taxonomy. The non-transferable product data type represents a product that can be traded (as part of a TradableProduct) but cannot be transferred to others.  It is meant to be used across the pre-execution, execution and (as part of the Contract) post-execution lifecycle contexts.
          economicTerms:
            description: The price forming features, including payouts and provisions.
            type:
              blueId: this#6
            schema:
              required: true
          identifier:
            description: Comprises a identifier and a source to uniquely identify the nonTransferableProduct.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: GFVh22HvpZREhKsn8HDuBiUrwRScVzwx6ZnNNmZrisx9
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          taxonomy:
            description: Specifies the product taxonomy, which is composed of a taxonomy value and a taxonomy source.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: 4Yp9gtVpX1NNhVLvRCpFGS3MvbUnmDXUmuAKSDYaTNWN
            schema:
              minItems: 0
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8uQuzNQKBLC5kpFy4UH3BU7PPtpbRZEfLQ2ftrsgLHbm#4
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionalEarlyTermination
          description: |
            A data defining:  an early termination provision where either or both parties have the right to exercise.
          calculationAgent:
            description: The ISDA Calculation Agent responsible for performing duties associated with an optional early termination.
            type:
              blueId: FANsoqTgc5XxJH7orWbzRADwZ6drQjPzAbPN6YqvcYau
          cashSettlement:
            description: |
              If specified, this means that cash settlement is applicable to the transaction and defines the parameters associated with the cash settlement procedure. If not specified, then physical settlement is applicable.
            type:
              blueId: 2qfdfn8VYJmiXxmTj9Vwfu1pB3jFJQK9WAShnf8n1r1m
          exerciseNotice:
            description: Definition of the party to whom notice of exercise should be given.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: JC1AzddnU2E4ioTzwsgW9ohgnrfpQQusp6hRq412YjUZ
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          exerciseTerms:
            description: |
              The exercise terms associated with the optional early termination, including details such as exercise style, exercise fees, and any other relevant conditions or terms.
            type:
              blueId: J1G2hQLDGZ1gu2re4Z6NCNRA3Ze9S9LM51pbnxyzozLq
            schema:
              required: true
          followUpConfirmation:
            description: |
              A flag to indicate whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.
            type:
              blueId: AwvXD961fmnmqcSQhjMA7r15HpVh39cefb6ZTyUz2Fm2
          mutualEarlyTermination:
            description: |
              Used for specifying whether the Mutual Early Termination Right that is detailed in the Master Confirmation will apply.
            type:
              blueId: AwvXD961fmnmqcSQhjMA7r15HpVh39cefb6ZTyUz2Fm2
          optionalEarlyTerminationAdjustedDates:
            description: |
              An early termination provision to terminate the trade at fair value where one or both parties have the right to decide on termination.
            type:
              blueId: GjM8odwxuvdr9Y58M4jULKzxi93AmZuKSFfkTFsJ7cYx
          singlePartyOption:
            description: |
              If optional early termination is not available to both parties then this component specifies the buyer and seller of the option. In FpML, this attribute is of type SinglePsrtyOption, which actually consists of the BuyerSeller.model.
            type:
              blueId: HA8fmtXcNJxs3hXa88H9PHchDg6hgAFvto4VVdW1aZmf
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 9qZESRoTw3JVrvChnNta2oj5TcTb7RV9ijcSRtnuCQvs
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionalEarlyTerminationAdjustedDates
          description: |
            A data defining:  the adjusted dates associated with an optional early termination provision.
          earlyTerminationEvent:
            description: The adjusted dates associated with an individual early termination date.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: 3wSwzEEsW9wqLsvHavDA1EwFMzMefG38hhcM1BgdrLr9
            schema:
              minItems: 1
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: GjM8odwxuvdr9Y58M4jULKzxi93AmZuKSFfkTFsJ7cYx
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionExerciseStyleEnum
          description: The enumerated values to specify the option exercise style. i.e., European, Bermuda or American.
          type:
            blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          schema:
            enum:
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: American
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Bermuda
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: European
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: E7G8rbJWZbrsWYs4MwRaciyoqUH3qB2cKFMgynJ8Jide
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionFeature
          description: Defines additional optional features that can be included in an option contract.
          averagingFeature:
            description: |
              Defines an option feature in which an average market observation price is determined on valuation and compared to the strike to determine a settlement amount.
            type:
              blueId: G81eqYsDuMYSpYk1hESW7JLhMtsEbDs8dVTux7zmXLUZ
          barrier:
            description: Specifies a barrier feature.
            type:
              blueId: BY44nAmZ3yv6hAhiK1EG57TXEZNquFC8QoiMLUBELm2h
          fxFeature:
            description: Describes a quanto or composite FX feature.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: HPRsaReKQuhsZQyFweRGJshuiWo9hd1r6CsmkM6iPQnN
            schema:
              minItems: 0
          knock:
            description: Specifies a knock in or knock out feature.
            type:
              blueId: 6BETyPG5V4U1TUp5rVWo3V4V47SDx9g18ekbAAYhpp4U
          passThrough:
            description: Specifies the rules for pass-through payments from the underlier, such as dividends.
            type:
              blueId: 48DkPx7UNHrRug36JutQfuqHBiEgcCS2XZiEbFZ4xi4q
          strategyFeature:
            description: Defines a simple strategy feature.
            type:
              blueId: 8Y5hzBqBHEUiwLTnEj3w34yWp3pZ7s2RiBzE2Mi9or3v
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: iFRGjqPC6ijQF491otn9biLkPW4na25mmZ7gGtFn2Fj
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionPayout
          description: |
            The option payout specification terms. The associated globalKey denotes the ability to associate a hash value to the respective OptionPayout instantiation for the purpose of model cross-referencing, in support of functionality such as the event effect and the lineage.
          buyerSeller:
            type:
              blueId: HA8fmtXcNJxs3hXa88H9PHchDg6hgAFvto4VVdW1aZmf
            schema:
              required: true
          delivery:
            description: Contains the information relative to the delivery of the asset.
            type:
              blueId: 78abSDet2v5nbbeXAmoFZG2ZcMhk4674b2vrAKGT3yiu
          exerciseTerms:
            description: |
              The terms for exercising the option, which include the option style (e.g. American style option), the exercise procedure (e.g. manual exercise) and the settlement terms (e.g. physical vs. cash).
            type:
              blueId: J1G2hQLDGZ1gu2re4Z6NCNRA3Ze9S9LM51pbnxyzozLq
            schema:
              required: true
          feature:
            description: The option feature, such as quanto, Asian, barrier, knock.
            type:
              blueId: iFRGjqPC6ijQF491otn9biLkPW4na25mmZ7gGtFn2Fj
          observationTerms:
            description: |
              Class containing terms that are associated with observing a price/benchmark/index across either single or multple observations. To be used for option contracts that reference a benchmark price.
            type:
              blueId: 9pJEidhmAUQebdR3uTioauH2mNHR8RLS9r7xaB9vxpRd
          optionType:
            description: |
              The type of option transaction. From a usage standpoint, put/call is the default option type, while payer/receiver indicator is used for options on index credit default swaps, consistently with the industry practice. Straddle is used for the case of straddle strategy, that combine a call and a put with the same strike.
            type:
              blueId: 8ErhA2L9qAVdWjMVzZuXRSZDWRC2HdhAZCUsa4qbaya4
          payerReceiver:
            description: Canonical representation of the payer and receiver parties applicable to each payout leg.
            type:
              blueId: 3xPof2WJyFXisFtvaxpSGddTxHyGioazbsMJjuUucbzT
          priceQuantity:
            description: |
              Each payout leg must implement the quantity concept as a 'resolvable' type, which allows for different payout legs to be linked to each other (e.g. in the case of cross-curreny products).
            type:
              blueId: 7nSxNdghnPkGBbyqzqUELC5UcBMNfLdrCr4oXbav2d3J
          principalPayment:
            description: |
              The specification of the principal exchange. Optional as only applicable in the case of cross-currency or zero-coupon swaps with a final payment.
            type:
              blueId: 8VsQE5PSzyWWApw5Ykfum97vLPNoa36BemLUMHimzMb5
          schedule:
            description: |
              Allows the full representation of a payout by defining a set of schedule periods. It supports standard schedule customization by expressing all the dates, quantities, and pricing data in a non-parametric way.
            type:
              blueId: GbAmo8bxznHkBwFWFP6JMXCQEsWMyu9iKFV2KtBqH1rP
          settlementTerms:
            description: |
              Each payout leg must specifies its settlement terms, including the delivery type (i.e. cash vs physical, and their respective terms), the transfer type (DvP etc.) and settlement date, if any.
            type:
              blueId: 2qfdfn8VYJmiXxmTj9Vwfu1pB3jFJQK9WAShnf8n1r1m
          strike:
            description: Specifies the strike of the option
            type:
              blueId: 2dSkgwb8hLPVxQFwzcY81Rz3doMpbjGnxxouhx3k8wJ2
          underlier:
            description: |
              The financial product underlying the option, which can be of any type including an Asset, Basket, Index or a NonTransferableProduct.
            type:
              blueId: this#3
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8uQuzNQKBLC5kpFy4UH3BU7PPtpbRZEfLQ2ftrsgLHbm#7
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionStrike
          description: Defines the strike price of an option.
          averagingStrikeFeature:
            description: Defines an  option strike that is calculated from an average of observed market prices.
            type:
              blueId: HxYQ9z6xDVRw63wB5M3kiknebJ9fvTEFsXwtbJPtXRRD
          referenceSwapCurve:
            description: |
              Defines the strike of an option when expressed by reference to a swap curve (Typically the case for a convertible bond option).
            type:
              blueId: 2sDB91wA63tF5EXtQR9UbQQnyGu7CqG5AHbYURVxLHNc
          strikePrice:
            description: |
              Defines the strike of an option in the form of a price that could be a cash price, interestRate, or other types.
            type:
              blueId: GLmQaa2vVZKjaht1sNMcUL55xfAgWQxpj5ENxwvVRvsm
          strikeReference:
            description: |
              Defines the strike of an option in reference to the spread of the underlying swap (typical practice in the case of an option on a credit single name swaps).
            type:
              blueId: 9MuxTNnqdBfc2jXWLVxrcXeAQkmmc3aoj2AuNQ46RBnh
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 2dSkgwb8hLPVxQFwzcY81Rz3doMpbjGnxxouhx3k8wJ2
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/OptionTypeEnum
          description: The enumerated values to specify the type or strategy of the option.
          type:
            blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
          schema:
            enum:
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Call
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Payer
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Put
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Receiver
              - type:
                  blueId: GX7CFUmSDrE2MzptunLCCdZwnuwwrenRQqEnHL4x3uoC
                value: Straddle
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8ErhA2L9qAVdWjMVzZuXRSZDWRC2HdhAZCUsa4qbaya4
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/PartialExercise
          description: |
            A class defining partial exercise. As defined in the 2000 ISDA Definitions, Section 12.3 Partial Exercise, the buyer of the option may exercise all or less than all the notional amount of the underlying swap but may not be less than the minimum notional amount (if specified) and must be an integral multiple of the integral multiple amount if specified.
          integralMultipleAmount:
            description: |
              A notional amount which restricts the amount of notional that can be exercised when partial exercise or multiple exercise is applicable. The integral multiple amount defines a lower limit of notional that can be exercised and also defines a unit multiple of notional that can be exercised, i.e. only integer multiples of this amount can be exercised.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          minimumNotionalAmount:
            description: The minimum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date. See multipleExercise.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
          minimumNumberOfOptions:
            description: The minimum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date.
            type:
              blueId: E2LM6qgzWG9ttagq2xTmiZkgYEAgkYedFCmU9v7NnVEq
          notionaReference:
            description: |
              A pointer style reference to the associated notional schedule defined elsewhere in the document. This element has been made optional as part of its integration in the OptionBaseExtended, because not required for the options on securities.
            type:
              blueId: EP1r4ouVVbfJhEazX6iBArCJYk3u6aP7hwxJSGLBFbet
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: BpdSpKc8R5gAnDZQF7eJYbRNetxpvv1r1XSY9dh1LTaC
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/PassThrough
          description: Type which contains pass through payments.
          passThroughItem:
            description: One to many pass through payment items.
            type:
              blueId: 8DSFoWG9MqRSUhStqoPLrwVQiYByRh18NWbDEarN8MKF
            itemType:
              blueId: 6NM4Yn28gaQ8DzULANDLBBiyvCGXsVB8yFf3ZfqfPgCJ
            schema:
              minItems: 1
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 48DkPx7UNHrRug36JutQfuqHBiEgcCS2XZiEbFZ4xi4q
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/PassThroughItem
          description: Class to represent a single pass through payment.
          passThroughPercentage:
            description: Percentage of payments from the underlier which are passed through.
            type:
              blueId: 9eWaHYz2vKrFofdHTHAizNNu8xP6QE3WQ5y7DGrGZvyJ
            schema:
              required: true
          payerReceiver:
            description: This attribute doesn't exists in the FpML construct, which makes use of the PayerReceiver.model group.
            type:
              blueId: 3xPof2WJyFXisFtvaxpSGddTxHyGioazbsMJjuUucbzT
            schema:
              required: true
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 6NM4Yn28gaQ8DzULANDLBBiyvCGXsVB8yFf3ZfqfPgCJ
            attributesAdded: []
      - status: stable
        content:
          name: cdm/product/template/Payout
          description: |
            Represents the set of future cashflow methodologies in the form of specific payout data type(s) which result from the financial product.  Examples: a trade in a cash asset will use only a settlement payout; for derivatives, two interest rate payouts can be combined to specify an interest rate swap; one interest rate payout can be combined with a credit default payout to specify a credit default swap.
          AssetPayout:
            description: Defines the assets and movements in a security financing transaction.
            type:
              blueId: CaDUz9AY1EXhFRYQN73HdC98mAe18bh4BxACMShr4JNB
          CommodityPayout:
            description: Defines the payout for the floating leg of a Commodity Swap.
            type:
              blueId: this#5
          CreditDefaultPayout:
            description: |
              The credit default payout, which provides the details necessary for determining when a credit payout will be triggered as well as the parameters for calculating the payout and the settlement terms.
            type:
              blueId: AgZcx5eJYcy6vzz9NejmvMBuMpzza4tjH2bEtMYNkMVD
          FixedPricePayout:
            description: Defines a payout in which one or more payouts are defined as a fixed price.
            type:
              blueId: HGZMKY1yoBjBujWhaTqwBYYsw3GkD4w8Wc9G6D6nrDaa
          InterestRatePayout:
            description: |
              All of the terms necessary to define and calculate a cash flow based on a fixed, a floating or an inflation index rate. The interest rate payout can be applied to interest rate swaps and FRA (which both have two associated interest rate payouts), credit default swaps (to represent the fee leg when subject to periodic payments) and equity swaps (to represent the funding leg).
            type:
              blueId: 6JEZ2eR6XbPr27we4enAnhEA3t33WcEUzQSnH1uFWQ5Q
          OptionPayout:
            description: The option payout.
            type:
              blueId: this#7
          PerformancePayout:
            description: |
              The performance payout, which encompasses the equity price returns, dividend returns, volatility return, variance return and correlation provisions.
            type:
              blueId: this#1
          SettlementPayout:
            description: |
              Represents a forward settling payout. The 'Underlier' attribute captures the underlying payout, which is settled according to the 'SettlementTerms' attribute. Both FX Spot and FX Forward should use this component.
            type:
              blueId: this#2
        versions:
          - repositoryVersionIndex: 0
            typeBlueId: 8uQuzNQKBLC5kpFy4UH3BU7PPtpbRZEfLQ2ftrsgLHbm#9
